      • initGraphHead

        public TemporalGraphHead initGraphHead(GradoopId id,
                                       String label,
                                       Properties properties,
                                       Long validFrom,
                                       Long validTo)
        Initializes an graph head based on the given parameters. If the valid times are null, default values are used.
        Parameters:
        id - graph head identifier
        label - graph head label
        properties - graph head properties
        validFrom - begin of the elements validity as unix timestamp [ms] or null
        validTo - end of the elements validity as unix timestamp [ms] or null
        Returns:
        the edge instance

      • fromNonTemporalGraphHead

        public TemporalGraphHead fromNonTemporalGraphHead(GraphHead graphHead)
        Helper function to create a TPGM graph head from an EPGM graph head. The ids, label and all other information will be inherited.
        Parameters:
        graphHead - the EPGM graph head instance
        Returns:
        a TPGM graph head instance with default values at its valid times
